Don&#39;t forget to select your ESP8266 board from the Tools &gt; Board menu after installation.
    const int LED_RED = 5;void setup() { pinMode(LED_RED, OUTPUT); // setup red LED as output}void loop() { digitalWrite(LED_RED, LOW); // turn the LED on delay(1000); // wait for a second digitalWrite(LED_RED, HIGH); // turn the LED off delay(1000); // wait for a second}
 If all goes well the board will program and the red LED will start blinking.
